HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta Bayyana Karin Sabbin Cutar HIV da Kashi 14
Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar yawan mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suke fama da wannan cuta, in ji majiyoyin gwamnati.
An samu wasu sabbin mutane 40,000 a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka suna faruwa ne ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ya nuna canji daga baya.
A wasu yankuna na kasar Sin, cutar HIV ta yadu a baya sakamakon ƙarin jini da ke dauke da cutar.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar ta hanyar wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji hukumomin kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taron da aka yi a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i matsala ce mai tsanani a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An dakatar da nuna luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma har yanzu nuna wariya ga mutanen LGBT ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Domin al'adun ƙasar, wasu bincike sun nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin ɗari na maza da suka yi jima'i da maza suna aure.
