Masu gabatar da kara da ke kare Grace sun bayyana El Salvador, Honduras da Guatemala, wadanda ke samar da yawan masu neman mafaka a Amurka, a matsayin kasashen da ke fuskantar matsalar aikata laifuka da kuma tashin hankali a gida.
Sabuwar manufar neman mafaka ta Amurka ta sauya hukuncin da Hukumar Kula da Shige da Fice ta yanke a shekarar 2014 wanda ya ba da damar neman mafaka ga baƙi marasa izini da ke tserewa daga tashin hankali a cikin gida.
A ranar Juma'a, Babban Lauyan Gundumar Columbia, Karl Racine, ya ce sabuwar manufar ta yi watsi da shekarun da suka gabata na jihohi, tarayya da kuma dokokin duniya.
Dokar tarayya ta bukaci a yi hukunci a kan duk wani bukatar neman mafaka bisa ga takamaiman yanayi da kuma yanayin da ake nema, kuma irin wannan haramcin ya sabawa wannan ka'idar, in ji takardar amicus curiae.
A cikin takardar, masu gabatar da kara sun kuma yi jayayya cewa dokar hana shigowar baƙi tana cutar da tattalin arzikin Amurka, suna mai cewa suna da damar zama 'yan kasuwa da kuma samar da ma'aikata da ake buƙata.
A watan Yuni, Babban Lauyan Jeff Sessions ya umarci alƙalan shige da fice da su daina ba da mafaka ga waɗanda ke tserewa daga cin zarafin gida da kuma tashin hankali.
Sashen ya ce, asilo zai kasance ga waɗanda suka bar ƙasarsu saboda tsanantawa ko tsoron tseren, addini, ƙasa, ƙungiyar zamantakewa ko ra'ayin siyasa, Sessions ya bayyana a ranar 11 ga Yuni, a matsayin wani ɓangare na sanarwar siyasa.
