Kyaftin din Turai, Thomas Bjorn, ya san cewa fa'ida mai kyau tana iya ɓacewa da sauri.
Thomas Bjorn, kyaftin din Turai, ya san cewa babban ci gaba a wasan mutum-mutumi a ranar karshe ta gasar Ryder Cup zai iya zama matsala.
Dan Dan Dan ya fara wasa a wasan 1997 a Valderrama inda tawagar, wanda Seve Ballesteros ya jagoranci, duk da cewa ta kasance ta gaba da Amurkawa da maki biyar, ta isa layin ƙarshe tare da mafi ƙarancin nasara, ta lashe 141⁄2-131⁄2.
Na ci gaba da maimaita wa kaina cewa muna da kyakkyawar dama a Valderrama, muna da shi a Brookline, inda muka rasa, kuma a Valderrama inda muka ci nasara, amma kaɗan, in ji Bjorn (a hoto) bayan ya ga ajin 2018 sun ci nasara, Jumma'a da 5 zuwa 3 da jiya da 10 zuwa 6, a Le Golf National.
Saboda haka, tarihi zai nuna min da tawagarmu cewa ba a gama ba.
Dole ne mu yi iya ƙoƙarinmu a gobe.
Dole ne ku fita waje ku yi komai daidai.
Ba a gama ba har sai an rubuta maki a kan allon.
Manufarmu ita ce mu ci kofin, kuma wannan shi ne abin da ya kamata mu mai da hankali a kai.
A koyaushe ina mai da hankali ga 'yan wasa 12 da ke tawagarmu, amma na san waɗanda suke a ɗaya gefen, wato, 'yan wasan golf mafi kyau a duniya.
Bjorn ya yi farin ciki da yadda iyayensa suka yi tsere a filin wasan golf mai wuya, ya kara da cewa: Ba zan taɓa wuce kaina ba.
Amma gobe zai zama wani ƙalubale dabam.
Za a yi wasan kwaikwayo na mutum ɗaya gobe, wanda wani abu ne dabam.
